# GENZ configuration
#

menuconfig GENZ
	tristate "Gen-Z support"
	depends on SYSFS
	help
	  This option enables the Gen-Z fabric sub-system.  Gen-Z is an
	  hardware fabric interconnect that connects a broad range of
	  devices from CPUs, memory, I/O, and switches to other computers
	  and all of their devices.

	  Say Y here to enable support for these types of drivers.

	  To compile this code as a module, choose M here: the module
	  will be called genz.

if GENZ

config GENZ_BLK
	tristate "Gen-Z block driver"
	select DAX_DRIVER
	help
	  This option enables the Gen-Z block driver.

	  Say Y here to enable support for these types of devices.

	  To compile this code as a module, choose M here: the module
	  will be called genz-blk.

config GENZ_CTL
	tristate "Gen-Z control space mapping driver"
	depends on GENZ
	help
	  This option enables the Gen-Z control space mapping driver.

	  Say Y here to enable support for these types of devices.

	  To compile this code as a module, choose M here: the module
	  will be called genz-ctl.

source "drivers/genz/iprop/Kconfig"
source "drivers/genz/wildcat/Kconfig"
endif
